                    "company": "International journal: Creative Arts Education and Therapy - Frontiers in China (CAET)",
                    "description": "CAET is an international, peer reviewed journal featuring the cross disciplinary interactions and the latest development of the creative arts education and therapy in China.  The journal focuses on the research and practice in the area of education and psychotherapy related to various art forms including dance/movement, drama, music, poetry, the visual arts and other creative expressions and publishes original research articles, review articles, book reviews contributed from both Chinese and non-Chinese authors. The journal also reports news and comments on national and international conferences together with relevant educational and professional information.\n\nCAET publishes 2 issues per annum in English in both electronic and printed version with bilingual abstract (English and Chinese). The journal will be distributed to the major university and institute libraries, as well as the individual professionals, in China and worldwide for those interested in the research and practice of creative arts for education and psychotherapy.\n\u200b\u200b\nAs the first journal of its kind in the world, we expect CAET to become the major source in the research on the creative arts education and therapy in China and eventually being indexed in ISI etc.\n\nWe have some 40 recognized scholars in the editorial board including Professor Shaun McNiff (Editor in Chief, Lesley University, U.S.), Professoe Robert Landy (New York University), Professor Helen Payne (UK) and  Professor Michael Thaut (US).",
